# 1️⃣ Silver — Padronizado

## 🎯 Objetivo

Criar o **contrato técnico inicial do dado**:

- Padronizar nomes
    
- Expor partição física (`p_*`)
    
- Criar colunas temporais canônicas
    
- Manter chaves de negócio
    
- Preparar dado para reuso
    

📎 Referência do template:

---

## 1.1 Boletos pagos

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW workspace_db.view_silver_padronizado_cobranca_boletos AS
SELECT
    dt_ref AS p_dt_ref,

    cast(substr(cast(dt_ref as varchar), 1, 6) as integer) AS mes_ref_yyyymm,
    dt_ref AS dt_ref_yyyymmdd,
    cast(date_parse(cast(dt_ref as varchar), '%Y%m%d') as date) AS dt_ref_date,
    cast(date_parse(cast(dt_ref as varchar), '%Y%m%d') as timestamp) AS ts_ref,

    contrato,
    produto,
    cnpj_raiz,
    escritorio,

    boleto,
    vl_pago,
    vl_desconto_boleto,
    coalesce(flag_cancelado, 0) AS flag_cancelado,

    'BOLETO' AS origem_pagamento,
    cast(null as varchar) AS tp_acordo,

    current_timestamp AS dt_ingestao_modelo,
    'execucao_manual' AS id_execucao,

    md5(
        concat(
            coalesce(cast(contrato as varchar), ''),
            '|', coalesce(cast(produto as varchar), ''),
            '|', coalesce(cast(dt_ref as varchar), '')
        )
    ) AS hash_chave_negocio,

    md5(
        concat(
            coalesce(cast(boleto as varchar), ''),
            '|', coalesce(cast(vl_pago as varchar), ''),
            '|', coalesce(cast(vl_desconto_boleto as varchar), ''),
            '|', coalesce(cast(flag_cancelado as varchar), '')
        )
    ) AS hash_atributos
FROM workspace_db.tabela_bronze_fonte_sap_boletos;
```

